The paper proposes a generalizable approach for user-generated item list continuation, which involves modeling the consistency of item lists based on human curation patterns. This falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach also involves modeling user preferences, which can be seen as a sub-topic of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed model in the context of different types of item lists, such as books and answers, which could be classified under natural language processing (cs.CL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC), respectively.
